attributes.body:
Introduce your child to water in a playful and secure environment. In the infant program, a parent or carer supports the baby or toddler in the pool. This helps build confidence and supports the child's learning process.

Children will learn to:

  • be familiar with having water over their face and head
  • control their breath and blow bubbles
  • float, paddle and propel themselves.

Our swimming teachers

Our teachers hold nationally accredited swimming teacher and water safety certificates, and specialised qualifications for teaching infants. They have current CPR and first aid certificates, and have training in safeguarding children and young people.

Program levels

  • Buoyancy and flotation activities
  • Introduction to kicking and arm movement
  • Introduction to blowing bubbles
  • Deliberate movement towards a target
Level Description
Starfish
(6-12 months)
Class size: 8
  • Parent/carer in water with child
  • Parent/carer water safety education
  • Socialising with group activities
  • Water exploration activities
  • Buoyancy and flotation activities with attempted movement towards a target, with and without aids
Periwinkle
(1-2 years)
Class size: 8
  • Parent/carer in water with child
  • Parent/carer water safety education
  • Comfortable and confident in water
  • Independently follows simple requests
  • Comfortable and confident submersion on request
Minnow
(2-3 years)
Class size: 8

attributes.body:
YMCA helps people experiencing disadvantage by subsidising the costs of YMCA programs and services.

YMCA offers a great range of programs and services for people of all ages, abilities, cultural backgrounds and lifestyles. However, unfortunately not all people can afford to participate. YMCA Open Doors is in an initiative that provides full or partially subsidised access to YMCA programs or services for people in need.

It is part of our mission to provide equal access to health and wellness services to all members of the community, and help everyone lead healthier and happier lives.

If you or someone you know is experiencing financial difficulty, but would like to access the YMCA’s services, subsidies of 80-100% are available through YMCA Open Doors.

Terms and Conditions Safeguarding Children and Young People
At YMCA Victoria we are committed to providing a safe environment for all children and young people. Read our Safeguarding Children and Young People Policy.

Occupational Health and Safety policy
We recognise our legal, ethical and moral responsibilities to prevent work related injury and illness. The YMCA is committed to providing safe places of work that do not place the health and safety of any person at risk. Read our Occupational Health & Safety policy.

Environmental policy
YMCA Victoria is committed to building a thriving, prosperous, safe and sustainable Y. This includes a specific commitment to minimize our environmental impact and advocate for healthier environments.

YMCA Victoria acknowledges the importance of protecting the environment in a sustainable manner to help reduce any detrimental impact its operations and activities might have. YMCA is committed to ensuring this through the development, implementation and maintenance of an Environmental Management System, based on the international ISO14001 Standard. Read our Environmental Policy.

attributes.body:
In this program, the focus is on physical, intellectual and personal development. Children establish a lifelong appreciation for safe activity in the water, and learn vital survival skills not just for the pool but for rivers, lakes and the ocean.

Children will learn to:

  • develop and refine swimming strokes
  • cooperate with and respect others in an aquatic environment
  • make safe and sensible decisions and solve problems in and around water.

Our swimming teachers

All of our teachers hold nationally accredited swimming teacher and water safety certificates. They have current CPR and first aid certificates, and have training in safeguarding children and young people.

Program levels

Teachers assess and progress children through the program levels, based on their individual ability.

Octopus
(5+ years)
Class size: 5
  • Push and glide
  • Kick on front and back with aid 5 metres
  • Paddle and kick
  • Torpedo 3 metres
  • Treading water
Sardine
(5+ years)
Class size: 6
  • Jump entry into deep water and recover
  • Kick on front with aid and side breathing 10 metres
  • Kick on back 10 metres
  • Backstroke, freestyle and torpedo 5 metres
  • Float, scull and tread water for 30 seconds and signal for help
  • Duck dive
Salmon
(5+ years)
Class size: 8
  • Seated dive
  • Step in entry and recover
  • Freestyle and backstroke 12 metres
  • Survival backstroke with aid 5 metres
  • Breaststroke kick with aid 5 metres
  • Float, scull and tread water for 1 minute and signal for help
  • Duck dive, swim underwater for 3 metres and recover object
Tuna
(5+ years)
Class size: 6
  • Stride entry
  • Freestyle and backstroke 25 metres
  • Survival backstroke 25 metres
  • Breaststroke kick with breath 12 metres
  • Forward somersault
  • Crouch dive
Dolphin
(5+ years)
Class size: 7
  • Compact jump
  • Freestyle and backstroke 50 metres
  • Survival backstroke and breaststroke 25 metres
  • Tumble turn
  • Dolphin kick and sidestroke 12 metres
  • Shallow dive
Shark
(5+ years)
Class size: 8
  • Feet first surface dive
  • Freestyle and backstroke 100 metres
  • Survival backstroke and breaststroke 50 metres
  • Butterfly 15 metres
  • Sidestroke 25 metres
  • Using combination of strokes 400 metre swim
  • Clothed swim, flat, scull and tread water for 5 minutes, remove clothes and swim for 5 minutes
Junior & Senior Squad Swimming
(No age limit, ability based)
Class size: 12
Class duration: 1 hour
  • Focus on strong swimming skills and water safety
  • Strength, endurance and fitness training
  • Develops readiness for competition with stroke technique, education about competition rules and regular competitive swimming practice
Aqua-Guard
(12+ years)
Class duration: 1 hour
  • Suitable for confident swimmers who have passed all the levels but don’t want to swim competitively
  • Aims to develop students’ knowledge of safe water rescue and survival
  • Builds students’ skills for future employment in the aquatic industry
  • Develops water skills, water safety, knowledge and how to carry out aquatic rescues
  • Provides a fun and dynamic learning environment
  • Goal of achieving Bronze Medallion
Level Description

Requirements for this program

  • Bring bathers, towel, goggles (recommended, but not required) and dry clothes
  • Photos are allowed in the pool (never in the change room area) if you respect others' privacy and get their consent
attributes.title: School-age Swimming Lessons

attributes.body:
It's never too late to learn how to swim. Our aim is to help you develop an appreciation for safe activity in the water, and learn vital survival skills not just for the pool but for rivers, lakes and the ocean.

  • Beginner classes develop water confidence through buoyancy and mobility. We'll gradually introduce steps to swimming.
  • Intermediate and advanced classes focus on stroke refinement and correction.

Our teachers are AUSTSWIM accredited, and provide a safe, social and encouraging learning environment.

Program levels

Our teachers will assess your abilities to get you started in the right program level and continue to assess your skills in class to help you progress you through the program levels.

Level
 Description
Beginner

For adults with very little water experience

  • Focuses on building confidence in the water
  • Buoyancy and flotation techniques
  • Introduction to strokes
  • Deliberate movement towards a target
  • Confident submersions
Intermediate

For adults with some water experience

  • Starting to swim confidently
  • Stroke refinement
  • Freestyle and backstroke to 12 metres
Advanced

For adults with water experience who want to improve their stroke technique

  • Stroke refinement and correction: freestyle, backstroke, breaststroke
  • Focuses on improving swimming distance

To enquiry complete the form on this page or call us on (03) 5722 1723
attributes.title: Adult Swimming Lessons

attributes.body:
In the preschool swimming program, children learn to become more independent in the water and begin to develop important water survival skills.

Children will learn skills in:

  • body orientation
  • propulsion and submersion
  • basic stroke development
  • personal and water safety.

Our swimming teachers

Our teachers hold nationally accredited swimming teacher and water safety certificates. They have current CPR and first aid certificates, and have training in safeguarding children and young people.

Program levels

Teachers assess and progress children through the program levels, based on their individual ability.

Tadpole
(3-5 years)
Class size:5
  • Push and glide with bubbles
  • Independent submersion with bubbles
  • Aided jump entry and return to edge
  • Extended arm paddle
  • Aided kick on front and back
  • Aided treading water
  • Torpedo 3 metres
Goldfish
(3-5 years)
Class size: 5
  • Jump entry and return to edge
  • Independent rollover
  • Recover object from chest-deep water
  • Torpedo 3 metres
  • Freestyle and backstroke arms
  • Tread water for 15 seconds
Flying fish
(3-5 years)
Class size: 5
  • Step in entry and recover
  • Freestyle and backstroke 10 metres
  • Introduction to breaststroke, survival backstroke and butterfly kick
  • Duck dive, swim underwater for 3 metres and recover an object
  • Throw a buoyant aid and direct a partner to safety
Level Description

Requirements for this program

  • Children in nappies must wear aqua nappies that are tight fitting around the thighs (you can buy them here)
  • Bring bathers, towel, goggles (recommended, but not required) and dry clothes
  • Parents should bring bathers during the first few lessons, in case the child gets upset and needs support in the water
  • Photos are allowed in the pool (never in the change room area) if you respect others' privacy and get their consent

Host your child's next birthday party at WISAC, with five exciting themes to choose from.

Our parties are perfect for children aged 5-13 years old. We'll organise everything - the entertainment, catering and clean-up - so you can just sit back and enjoy the day. Beyond birthdays, our parties are also great team building activities for school groups, sports teams and social clubs.

We have five party themes for your child to choose from:

  • Dance party
  • Games party
  • Pool party
  • Sports party
  • Mega splash party with our 14m long inflatable

Dance party

Dance parties are held upstairs in the aerobics studio. The children can enjoy dance games to music such as ‘freeze’ and ‘statues’. The children can get their groove on in a fun atmosphere with age-appropriate music.

Games party

This party is full of traditional and new party games, led by our experienced party instructors - including games such as ‘Simon says’, ‘Musical chairs’, ‘Tiggy’, and ‘Poison ball’, just to name a few. The focus is on fun and everyone getting a go and having a great time.

Pool party

In a section of the pool reserved exclusively for the birthday party group, the kids can enjoy fully supervised pool time with age-appropriate games and activities and some free swim time.

Please note: children must be competent swimmers (according to their age). If not, a parent is welcome to provide additional assistance in the water. Party supervisors are not responsible for younger children or those not participating in the activities.

Sports party

A sports party consists of age-appropriate activities focused on a sport of your choice - including soccer, basketball, netball or badminton.

Mega splash party

Enjoy a fun-filled three hour party hosted by our Birthday Party Instructors - the kids love our 14 metre long giant pool inflatable - fun guaranteed! The mega splash birthday parties also include party food and games.

Beyond birthdays, our parties are also great team building activities for school groups, sports teams and social clubs.

attributes.body:
Swimming lessons programs at WISAC can be tailored to suit the needs of school groups.

Our YMCA Swimming Lessons Program is fully mapped to and aligned with Victorian Essential Learning Standards. We provide programs suitable for primary or secondary school students. In a practical environment students will develop physical skills, knowledge and understanding of a range of aquatic situations and participate in essential water safety and survival skills education.

Programs Our programs are flexible to suit your needs. Choose from a range of program lengths, teacher/student ratios, structures and activities, all run by nationally qualified instructors. Custom programs can include:

  • AquaSafe Theory – within school
  • AquaSafe Aquatic Education – with a focus on water safety and personal survival
  • Water polo – introductory skills and drills

Enquires and bookings can be made by contacting one of our friendly customer service team on (03) 5722 1723.

How it works

Classes are usually run in the following format:

  • Children are assessed at the start of the program and placed in their correct group for the duration of the program
  • The program runs for approximately 10 weeks during the school term
  • Classes run once a week for around 30 minutes
  • Classes have a teacher to student ratio of 1:10

We can tailor a program suitable for your school's needs. Contact our reception to find out more.

School carnivals and events

Whether you’re looking for a fun excursion or end of year event for your students, a venue for your swimming carnival, or an integrated component of your PE program, we are here to help.

Please get in contact with our customer service team on (03) 5722 1723.

We're committed to providing access to all students At the YMCA we are committed to providing every student with equal opportunity to participate in all programs. We can assist students with medical conditions and special needs, and also provide subsidised access to families with financial hardship.

Teachers please note:

We are also available to assist with your professional development, certification and skill-refreshers in

    AUSTSWIM CPR First aid

attributes.body:
WISAC is proud to offer YMCA Swimming Lessons, the leading Victorian provider of swimming lessons.

For more than 100 years YMCA has been teaching Victorians of all ages to swim, and inspiring children to develop a lifelong love of the water. Our swimming lesson program strives to ensure all students create a positive connection to the water and its surrounds, and helps them develop vital lifesaving survival skills, not for just the pool, but rivers, lakes and the ocean.

attributes.body:
Gymnastics is the perfect activity to prepare children for long-term participation in sport and helps to develop the fundamental movement skills for life.

Children who participate in gymnastics will benefit from:

  • Enhanced development of fundamental movement patterns
  • Enhanced flexibility
  • The ability to learn how to jump, land and fall safely
  • Increase in balance
  • An increase to both aerobic and anaerobic endurance
  • Unique long-term bone forming and strengthening advantages
  • Building self-esteem, preparing the body and mind for life’s challenges

Play Gym - Ages 18 months - 5 years

Play Gym is offered Wednesday mornings and afternoons during the school terms in the WISAC stadium. Play Gym is our interactive physical movement class specially designed for toddlers and preschoolers. The program includes activities to stimulate body awareness, co-ordination and general physical movement. The atmosphere is bright, interactive and age-appropriate.

Children must be assisted by a parent or carer.

attributes.body:
Our child care program is open to members and casual visitors seeking care for their children.

Children are supervised by qualified carers in our dedicated child care area, an interactive space equipped with games, toys and an outdoor play area. We provide children with the opportunity to socialise in a family/multi-age setting, where they can explore new experiences in a stimulating and caring environment. We welcome children from 6 months through their preschool years.

At WISAC, we offer two child care sessions per day on Mondays, Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Fridays. Sessions are 1.5 hours long and parents and carers are welcome to book one or both sessions per day. Our childcare service is available for infant and pre-school age children, while you enjoy the facilities at the WISAC, or simply while you take a break.

With over 50 live group fitness classes per week plus 100s of virtual classes to choose from, there's plenty of opportunity for you to get fit and have fun. Plus virtual fitness is available to eligible members 24/7.

attributes.title: Prices

attributes.body:
We have a wide range of facilities on offer to help you achieve your fitness goals. Train in our fully equipped gym, go for a swim in one of our two pools, or enjoy a healthy snack at our cafe.

Aquatic Facilities

Our 25 metre lap and recreational pool, toddler play pool, and warm water pool are indoors and open for swimming year-round.

24/7 Gym

Our fully equipped gym has a range of cardio, functional and resistance equipment for use, with a team of fully qualified fitness professionals on hand to assist you reach your goals.

Group Fitness Studios

We offer a huge range of instructor lead and virtual group fitness classes across our health club, fitness studios and cycle room. So whether you want to work up a sweat, build strength, or unwind with yoga, you're sure to find something you love.

Sporting Facilities

We have a range of sporting facilities to hire including a stadium that can facilitate badminton, basketball, netball and gymnastics, along with 6 squash courts.

Cafe

Whether you need an energy hit or a space to relax while the kids are in swimming lessons, @Charlies cafe has you covered. Re-energise with a range of fresh food, hot and cold snacks, cool drinks and barista-made coffee.
attributes.title: Facilities

attributes.body:
WISAC welcomes members and visitors to use its range of facilities and services.

We run over 50 group fitness classes each week, offer swimming lessons to people of all ages and abilities, and provide child care services in a safe and engaging environment.

Location We are conveniently located in HP Barr Reserve, Schilling Drive, Wangaratta. Bus route 403 stops outside the centre. There is also plenty of free parking available on site.

Opening hours
Monday - Friday 6:00am - 9:00pm
Saturday 8:00am - 7:00pm
Sunday 8:30am - 7:00pm
Inducted members are able to use the Gym and Virtual Fitness facilities 24/7.

Accessibility WISAC is well equipped to cater for people of all abilities including;

    A hoist and ramp for entering the warm water pool Accessible change room hoist Two accessible family/disabled change rooms Accessible parking close to the centre
Our friendly team are highly qualified and they have the experience to help you reach your training goals – whatever they may be. Our staff are there for you.

Partnership WISAC is owned by the Rural City of Wangaratta and managed by YMCA Victoria. As a YMCA community centre, we understand the needs of our members and visitors. We work with a number of community, sports and government bodies to offer opportunities for all our participants. YMCA is the leader in community and recreation facility management. We aim to provide the best in community care and services.

YMCA Open Doors – financial assistance YMCA Victoria helps local people in need become healthier, happier and more connected to their community. We focus on positive change and believe that everybody has a right to equal access to physical, mental and social well-being.

While hundreds of thousands of Victorians access YMCA programs or services on a weekly basis, we are concerned about the vast number who cannot due to their social and economic situations. By supporting the Y through donating, volunteering or fundraising, you are helping to provide access to opportunities for all people to grow in body, mind and spirit.

Contact us today to find out how you can help.

Nutrition We are committed to help you and your family live a healthier and happier life through more informed food and health choices. To support this goal, we have developed an exciting Nutrition Program in partnership with Australia’s leading network of nutrition experts, n4 food and health.
attributes.title: About Us

attributes.body: We are open to members and casual visitors seven days a week. Our facilities include multiple pools, a fully-equipped gym, sports centre, child care facilities and a cafe. We are easily accessible via public transport or car, with plenty of free parking available on site.

attributes.body:
The key to staying motivated is finding something you enjoy, which is why we offer a huge range of classes for all ages and fitness levels at WISAC.

We hold over 50 live classes every week in our group fitness rooms plus 100s of virtual classes, with a mix of high-energy and lower-impact classes to suit all ages and fitness levels. Classes range from 30-55 minutes, so everyone has time to fit in a workout. See a live schedule of virtual classes on the free Fitness on demand app.
